          "critical": false,
          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "A Pulmonary Embolism Response Team (PERT) provides rapid multidisciplinary decision-making for intermediate and high-risk PE, coordinating between emergency medicine, pulmonology, hematology, interventional radiology, and cardiac surgery. PERT activation is indicated for submassive PE with RV dysfunction or massive PE \u2014 the team determines whether catheter-directed thrombolysis, surgical embolectomy, or ECMO is most appropriate.",
