          "teaching": "Securing the ruptured aneurysm within 24\u201372 hours is the single most important intervention in SAH \u2014 rebleeding carries 40\u201370% mortality and occurs in up to 20% of untreated patients within the first 24 hours. Endovascular coiling is preferred over surgical clipping for most aneurysms based on ISAT trial data, but anatomy and location guide the decision.",
