    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "Time is brain \u2014 every minute of ischemia = ~1.9 million neurons lost",
      "IV tPA (alteplase): within 4.5 hours of symptom onset, NIHSS >4, no hemorrhage on CT",
      "Mechanical thrombectomy: within 24 hours for large vessel occlusion with salvageable tissue",
      "Must check: glucose (hypoglycemia mimic), INR, platelets, CT before tPA",
      "AFib without anticoagulation is the most preventable cause of ischemic stroke",
      "NIHSS standardizes severity \u2014 >15 suggests large vessel occlusion"
    ],
    "mustNotMiss": [
      "Hemorrhagic stroke (CT first \u2014 tPA is contraindicated)",
      "Hypoglycemia (check glucose immediately \u2014 most common stroke mimic)",
      "Todd paralysis (post-seizure \u2014 get history of seizure)",
      "Aortic dissection with carotid extension"
    ],
