          "id": "urosepsis-dist-1",
          "name": "Oral antibiotics only (outpatient)",
          "group": "Antibiotics",
          "correct": false,
          "critical": false,
          "phase": 0,
          "teaching": "Septic shock requires IV antibiotics and inpatient ICU-level management \u2014 oral antibiotics and outpatient treatment are absolutely contraindicated. Septic shock has 20\u201340% mortality even with optimal inpatient care. The first hour bundle (cultures, IV antibiotics, IV fluids, vasopressors) cannot be delivered outpatient.",
