    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "Adrenal crisis = hypotension refractory to IV fluids + known or suspected adrenal insufficiency \u2192 GIVE STRESS-DOSE STEROIDS IMMEDIATELY",
      "Treatment: IV hydrocortisone 100mg STAT bolus, then 50mg IV every 8 hours. At stress doses, hydrocortisone provides adequate mineralocorticoid activity \u2014 fludrocortisone not needed acutely",
      "Adrenal crisis triad: hypotension + hyponatremia + hyperkalemia (with hypoglycemia and eosinophilia)",
      "DO NOT wait for cortisol results before treating \u2014 clinical diagnosis, give steroids first",
      "Precipitants: medication non-compliance, intercurrent illness without stress-dosing, surgery, trauma, adrenal hemorrhage",
      "Hyperpigmentation (skin + mucosal) = PRIMARY adrenal insufficiency (high ACTH stimulates melanocytes). Secondary (pituitary) has no hyperpigmentation."
    ],
