          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Cold water immersion (15\u201317\u00b0C) is the gold standard cooling method for exertional heat stroke, achieving cooling rates of 0.15\u20130.35\u00b0C/min \u2014 far superior to ice packs, evaporative cooling, or cooling blankets. Target core temperature (rectal) <39\u00b0C within 30 minutes. Every minute above 40\u00b0C increases organ damage.",
