    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "Heat stroke = core temp >104\u00b0F (40\u00b0C) + CNS DYSFUNCTION (confusion, seizure, coma). AMS is what distinguishes heat stroke from heat exhaustion.",
      "COOL FIRST, TREAT SECOND \u2014 aggressive cooling is the single most important intervention. Target <102.2\u00b0F (39\u00b0C) within 30 minutes.",
      "Cold water immersion (CWI) is the gold standard \u2014 immerse to neck in ice water bath. Cooling rate: 0.15-0.35\u00b0C/minute. This is far superior to ice packs, evaporative cooling, or cold IV fluids alone.",
      "Exertional heat stroke (young, healthy, exercising) vs. Classic heat stroke (elderly, medications, no exertion) \u2014 exertional has higher rhabdomyolysis and DIC rates.",
      "Monitor for DIC (liver failure produces coagulopathy), rhabdomyolysis with AKI, hepatic failure (peaks 48-72h), and ARDS.",
      "Stop cooling at 102\u00b0F (38.9\u00b0C) to avoid overshoot hypothermia."
    ],
