          "teaching": "Surgical pericardial window is preferred for recurrent malignant effusions, loculated collections not accessible by needle, and hemorrhagic tamponade requiring source control. It provides continuous drainage and allows pericardial biopsy for tissue diagnosis when etiology is unclear.",
