      "Not checking for pulsus paradoxus \u2014 it's easy to measure and highly suggestive",
      "Waiting for cardiology to arrive before performing pericardiocentesis in an unstable patient \u2014 if the patient is crashing, emergent bedside drainage is indicated",
      "Not sending pericardial fluid for cytology \u2014 this may be the first diagnosis of cancer or confirm metastatic disease",
      "Assuming effusion = tamponade \u2014 size doesn't determine tamponade; RATE of accumulation determines hemodynamic impact. Slow effusions can be massive without tamponade; rapid effusions can cause tamponade with small volumes."
