          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Many migraine patients are significantly dehydrated from nausea, vomiting, and reduced oral intake during the prodrome and attack. IV fluid hydration with 1L normal saline can improve headache intensity independently of medication, by restoring cerebral perfusion and reducing vasomotor instability. It also facilitates IV medication delivery and reduces rebound nausea.",
