          "teaching": "Carotid ultrasound is NOT indicated in the workup of syncope. Carotid stenosis causes focal neurological deficits and TIA, not syncope. Ordering it reflects a common diagnostic error. Syncope is a transient global cerebral hypoperfusion event; carotid disease does not produce global hypoperfusion.",
