          "teaching": "HSV is the precipitating cause in >50% of erythema multiforme cases \u2014 recurrent EM is almost always HSV-triggered. Oral acyclovir (400 mg TID x5\u20137 days) or valacyclovir (500 mg BID) treats the active HSV infection driving the immune complex-mediated skin reaction. Drug-triggered EM accounts for fewer than 10% of cases; unnecessarily stopping medications is a common error. Always ask about preceding cold sores or genital herpes.",
