          "teaching": "Serum tryptase drawn 1\u20133 hours after anaphylaxis onset reflects total mast cell burden \u2014 a persistently elevated baseline tryptase (>11.4 ng/mL confirmed on a sample drawn >24 hours after the reaction) warrants evaluation for systemic mastocytosis, which dramatically increases anaphylaxis severity and venom immunotherapy reaction risk. All sting anaphylaxis patients should have a baseline tryptase checked.",
