          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "A detailed allergy history is essential to identify the true trigger \u2014 many apparent peanut reactions involve cross-contamination, hidden ingredients (lupin flour, mixed nuts), or cofactors (exercise, NSAIDs, alcohol) that lower the reaction threshold. Without a thorough history, dietary avoidance counseling will be inaccurate and the patient may remain at risk from unidentified triggers or unnecessarily restrict safe foods.",
