          "teaching": "Oral food challenge (OFC) is the gold standard for diagnosing food allergy and for determining whether tolerance has developed over time. It is performed in a controlled medical setting with resuscitation equipment available. OFC is essential to avoid unnecessary dietary restriction in patients who may have outgrown their allergy \u2014 approximately 20% of peanut-allergic children develop tolerance by early adulthood.",
