          "teaching": "Intranasal corticosteroids (fluticasone, mometasone, budesonide) reduce nasal mucosal inflammation and slow polyp regrowth in AERD. High-volume nasal irrigation with budesonide solution (budesonide respules in saline) delivers steroid directly to sinus mucosa. Nasal steroids are essential maintenance therapy but insufficient alone \u2014 LTRA therapy and aspirin desensitization address the underlying leukotriene dysregulation.",
