          "teaching": "Allergen immunotherapy (subcutaneous SCIT or sublingual SLIT) is the only disease-modifying treatment for allergic rhinitis \u2014 it desensitizes the immune system to specific allergens over a 3\u20135 year course, achieving durable remission that persists after treatment completion. It reduces medication requirements, prevents new sensitizations, and decreases the risk of progression to asthma. It is indicated for moderate-severe persistent AR that is inadequately controlled on pharmacotherapy.",
