          "correct": false,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Empiric antibiotics for uncontrolled allergic rhinitis without clinical evidence of bacterial sinusitis are inappropriate and contribute to antibiotic resistance. Allergic rhinitis is driven by IgE-mediated inflammation, not bacteria. Bacterial sinusitis is distinguished by purulent nasal discharge, facial pressure/pain, anosmia, and fever \u2014 findings not present in routine allergic rhinitis. INCS is the cornerstone of treatment; antibiotics have no role in uncomplicated AR.",
