          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Chronic systemic corticosteroids are not recommended for long-term CSU management \u2014 the side-effect burden of prolonged steroid use (adrenal suppression, osteoporosis, weight gain, hyperglycemia, immunosuppression) vastly outweighs the benefit when effective steroid-sparing options exist. Omalizumab 300 mg SC monthly is the evidence-based step-up therapy for antihistamine-refractory CSU and should be used instead.",
