          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Cow's milk protein elimination from the breastfeeding mother's diet is the first-line treatment for IgE-mediated or non-IgE-mediated (including FPIES) cow's milk allergy in breastfed infants. Maternal elimination of all dairy products (milk, cheese, butter, yogurt, hidden casein/whey) typically leads to symptom resolution within 2\u20134 weeks as cow's milk proteins clear from breast milk.",
