          "teaching": "Chronic FPIES is frequently misdiagnosed as gastroesophageal reflux disease \u2014 the vomiting, irritability, poor weight gain, and feeding aversion overlap substantially. PPIs will not improve FPIES and create unnecessary polypharmacy in infants. The distinguishing features of FPIES are the absence of response to antireflux therapy, the food-protein-triggered pattern, and resolution with dietary elimination.",
