          "teaching": "Breastfeeding should not be stopped for cow's milk protein allergy \u2014 breast milk remains the optimal nutrition for infants and provides immune, developmental, and bonding benefits. The appropriate intervention is maternal dietary elimination of all dairy products, which removes the sensitizing cow's milk proteins from breast milk within days. Weaning unnecessarily deprives the infant of the benefits of human milk.",
