          "teaching": "Re-challenging an infant with regular cow's milk formula to 'confirm' the allergy without an allergist-supervised oral food challenge risks another FPIES or allergic reaction in an infant who may already have significant GI compromise. The diagnosis is supported by clinical response to elimination \u2014 confirmation of tolerance should be done with a structured, supervised oral food challenge at the appropriate age (typically 12\u201318 months for CMPA, later for FPIES), not by informal home rechallenging.",
