          "correct": false,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Corticosteroids are ineffective for bradykinin-mediated angioedema \u2014 they reduce histamine-driven inflammation but have no effect on the kallikrein-bradykinin pathway responsible for ACE inhibitor angioedema or HAE. Their use is a common error that delays effective treatment with bradykinin-targeted agents (icatibant, C1-inhibitor concentrate) and may give false reassurance about clinical trajectory.",
