          "teaching": "IV fluid resuscitation with 1\u20132L isotonic crystalloid (normal saline or LR) rapidly corrects the distributive hypotension of anaphylaxis by replacing the intravascular volume lost to massive vasodilation and capillary leak. Use cautiously in elderly patients and those with known cardiac disease \u2014 aggressive fluid resuscitation can precipitate pulmonary edema in patients with impaired LV function.",
