          "teaching": "Aspirin desensitization \u2014 a graded hospital-based oral aspirin challenge starting at 20\u201340 mg and incrementally increasing to 325\u2013650 mg over 2\u20133 days \u2014 induces tolerance and enables daily aspirin therapy. Chronic high-dose aspirin (325\u2013650 mg BID) after desensitization dramatically reduces polyp regrowth, sinus surgery frequency, and asthma exacerbations. It is the most effective disease-modifying treatment for AERD.",
