          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "If K+ <3.5, hold insulin and replete potassium first \u2014 insulin drives K+ into cells and can cause fatal hypokalemia. DKA patients are always total body K+ depleted even if serum K+ is normal or high at presentation.",
