          "name": "Oral ciprofloxacin for septic pyelonephritis",
          "group": "Antibiotics",
          "critical": false,
          "correct": false,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Oral antibiotics are inappropriate for pyelonephritis complicated by sepsis \u2014 IV administration is required for reliable drug levels. Additionally, E. coli quinolone resistance rates now exceed 20-30% in many regions; empiric ceftriaxone IV is preferred. Oral therapy only after culture results confirm sensitivity and patient stabilizes.",
