          "teaching": "Ehrlichiosis classic triad: fever + leukopenia + thrombocytopenia + elevated LFTs. Morulae (intracytoplasmic inclusion bodies) in monocytes on peripheral smear \u2014 pathognomonic but seen in only 20-30% of cases. PCR most sensitive in first week.",
