          "teaching": "Fluid restriction is the primary treatment for SIADH \u2014 by restricting free water intake below urine output, the excess water is eliminated and sodium rises. Goal: restrict to 500-800 mL/day. Correction rate: <10-12 mEq/L per 24h to prevent osmotic demyelination syndrome.",
