          "group": "Airway",
          "critical": true,
          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Mechanical ventilation is definitive treatment for flail chest \u2014 positive pressure provides internal pneumatic splinting of the flailing segment. Indications: SpO2 <90% on high-flow O2, respiratory fatigue, pulmonary contusion >25%, shock, associated injuries. PEEP stabilizes alveoli in pulmonary contusion.",
