          "group": "Anticoagulation",
          "critical": true,
          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Cervical artery dissection (CAD) treatment: anticoagulation to prevent thrombus propagation and embolic stroke. Start UFH then transition to warfarin or DOAC x3-6 months. The arterial dissection itself forms a thrombus in the false lumen which can embolize. Antiplatelet therapy (aspirin) is an alternative per CADISS trial \u2014 no clear superiority of anticoagulation over antiplatelet.",
