          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Joint aspiration is both diagnostic and therapeutic. Positively birefringent rhomboid crystals = CPPD (pseudogout). Strongly negative needle-shaped = gout (uric acid). WBC 2,000-100,000 (inflammatory). Crystal finding does NOT exclude septic arthritis \u2014 always send culture.",
