          "teaching": "Blunt aortic injury: permissive hypotension (SBP 80-90 mmHg) until aortic repair \u2014 avoid aggressive fluid resuscitation that raises BP and risks rupture. This is called 'damage control resuscitation.' Rate control (HR <80) also reduces aortic wall stress.",
