          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Drug-induced AV block is REVERSIBLE \u2014 the single most important step is identifying and stopping the offending drug. Drugs causing AV block: beta-blockers, calcium channel blockers (non-DHP), digoxin, amiodarone, ivabradine. Combination of two AV nodal blocking drugs dramatically increases risk. Block resolves after drug clearance.",
