          "teaching": "Prosthetic hip dislocation: emergent closed reduction under procedural sedation within 6 hours \u2014 prolonged dislocation risks avascular necrosis, sciatic nerve injury, and damage to the prosthesis. Posterior dislocation (most common, 90%): hip flexed + internally rotated + adducted. Anterior: extension + external rotation.",
