          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "Aggressive NS hydration is the cornerstone of rhabdomyolysis treatment \u2014 flushes myoglobin from renal tubules before it precipitates and causes AKI. Target urine output 200-300 mL/h (3-4 mL/kg/h). Start at 1-1.5 L/h initially. Continue until CK <1000 and urine clears.",
