          "teaching": "Topical steroids are CONTRAINDICATED in bacterial keratitis \u2014 they suppress the immune response, promote bacterial replication, and increase corneal melt and perforation risk. Never use steroid eye drops before excluding bacterial or fungal infection. Steroids are used later only under ophthalmologist supervision after infection is controlled.",
