          "correct": true,
          "phase": 1,
          "teaching": "PET-CT is the standard staging tool for NSCLC \u2014 identifies mediastinal nodal involvement (N staging) and distant metastases (M staging). SUV >2.5 in mediastinal nodes suggests malignancy but false positives occur (inflammatory). Brain MRI or CT for stage III/IV (CNS mets common in lung cancer).",
